# Project Memory

This project uses `docs/obsidian` as an Obsidian vault for durable project memory.

Before large changes, read:

- `docs/obsidian/Home.md`
- `docs/obsidian/Architecture.md`
- `docs/obsidian/API Map.md`
- `docs/obsidian/Production Roadmap.md`

When code changes alter architecture, APIs, production setup, or important behavior, update the matching note in `docs/obsidian`.

Use these notes as the memory map:

- `Architecture.md`: stack, entry points, frontend/backend modules, database model.
- `API Map.md`: routes, auth behavior, request/response expectations.
- `Production Roadmap.md`: production hardening and rewrite plan.
- `Feature Backlog.md`: feature ideas and improvements.
- `Decision Log.md`: durable technical decisions and why they were made.
- `Session Notes.md`: concise summaries of meaningful work.

Do not store secrets, tokens, passwords, customer data, or local-only credentials in memory notes.
